# Val Ark - local configuration template
#
# Copy this to ".env" (which is git-ignored) and edit for your machine:
#     cp .env.example .env
#
# Nothing host-specific is ever committed; .env holds YOUR paths only.
# All values are optional — Val Ark autodetects sensible defaults if unset.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DATA ROOT — the disk Val Ark fills and measures free space against.
# Models live at   $VAL_ARK_DATA/models   (reused if already present)
# Everything else  $VAL_ARK_DATA/val-ark/{tools,content,sources,assets,installers,state}
#
# If unset, Val Ark autodetects the largest writable mount (/mnt/*, /data, ...),
# falling back to the repo directory for single-disk / dev use.
# VAL_ARK_DATA=/mnt/bigdisk
# VAL_ARK_DATA=/srv/val-ark
# VAL_ARK_DATA=$HOME/val-ark-data

# Extra autodetect candidates (colon-separated), tried before the built-ins.
# VAL_ARK_DATA_CANDIDATES=/mnt/bigdisk:/data2

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DISK RESERVE — never fill past this. Keeps the OS/disk healthy and leaves
# headroom for the "cut back for smaller valuable files" curation rule.
# Reserve = max(VALARK_RESERVE_PCT% of total, VALARK_RESERVE_MIN_GB).
# VALARK_RESERVE_PCT=2
# VALARK_RESERVE_MIN_GB=50

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# FINE-GRAINED OVERRIDES (rarely needed) — point individual trees elsewhere.
# VALARK_MODELS_DIR=/mnt/disk-a/models
# VALARK_TOOLS_DIR=/mnt/disk-b/tools
# VALARK_CONTENT_DIR=/mnt/disk-c/content

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# WEB UI / API — port the server (scripts/server.js) listens on.
# Set this if 3000 is taken; scripts/loop.sh and verify.sh honor it too.
# VALARK_WEB_PORT=3000
#
# Serve on a standard port too (http://<host>/ with no :3000). The loop keeps an
# idempotent iptables NAT redirect public->web port in place (all real
# interfaces: LAN + tailscale/VPN; loopback untouched, so an appliance's own
# 127.0.0.1:80 UI keeps working). Needs root or passwordless sudo for iptables.
# VALARK_WEB_PUBLIC_PORT=80
#
# Additional ports for the server to LISTEN on directly (comma-separated).
# Unlike the NAT redirect above this binds real sockets; ports <1024 need
#   sudo setcap 'cap_net_bind_service=+ep' $(command -v node)
# and a wildcard :80 bind fails if anything else holds 80 on ANY address.
# VALARK_WEB_EXTRA_PORTS=8080,8081

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# TOOL REFRESH — the loop re-runs the tool mirror every N days so mirrored apps
# track their latest upstream versions (0 = never). Each pass is bounded by
# VALARK_TOOL_REFRESH_TIMEOUT seconds and resumes next time if cut short.
# VALARK_TOOL_REFRESH_DAYS=7
# VALARK_TOOL_REFRESH_TIMEOUT=7200

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# STALE PARTIAL GC — failed librarian downloads keep their .part (+ aria2 .aria2
# control file) so multi-GB downloads resume across loop cycles instead of
# restarting from byte 0. A partial untouched for this many days (dead URL,
# catalog rotation) is deleted by `librarian.sh verify`. Active retries refresh
# the file every cycle, so only genuinely abandoned partials age out.
# VALARK_PARTIAL_MAX_AGE_DAYS=14

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ZIM LANGUAGES — which Kiwix ZIM languages the catalog includes (space-separated).
# Default: eng spa fra deu rus ara hin zho por
# VALARK_ZIM_LANGS="eng spa fra deu rus ara hin zho por"

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# COMMUNITY SERVICES (chat, mail, message boards, files/pastebin). Val Ark can
# run these LAN-bound and frame them in the web shell at /app/<id>/. See
# docs/COMMUNITY.md. Mirror a service with scripts/tools/<id>.sh, then enable it
# here so the loop keeps it running. Empty = none enabled.
# VALARK_SERVICES="paste"
# VALARK_SERVICES="chat mail forum paste"
#
# Bind address for service LAN ports (the web UIs always stay on 127.0.0.1 and
# are reached only via the reverse proxy). 0.0.0.0 = whole LAN; 127.0.0.1 = host-only.
# VALARK_BIND=0.0.0.0
#
# Per-service admin/login overrides (otherwise generated on first run):
# VALARK_CHAT_ADMIN_USER=admin
# VALARK_CHAT_ADMIN_PASS=change-me
# VALARK_FORUM_ADMIN_USERNAME=admin
# VALARK_FORUM_ADMIN_PASSWORD=change-me
# VALARK_FORUM_ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@valark.lan
# PASTE_AUTH_USER=valark
# PASTE_AUTH_PASSWORD=change-me
# PASTE_ADMIN_PASSWORD=change-me

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CONTENT MODERATION — the self-heal loop screens already-stored uploads with the
# box's own offline classifier and quarantines anything flagged into an admin
# review queue (Safety card). Screening is ON by default (fail-closed), but the
# loop's enforcement SWEEP only touches a PLAIN-FILE tree you explicitly point it
# at: with neither key set, `mod-sweep.sh` logs "no upload dirs to screen" and does
# nothing. It deliberately never sweeps a service's DB-backed store (MicroBin
# SQLite, maddy mail) — moving a DB-referenced file would corrupt the store.
#
# The dedicated uploads / drop area to sweep (one plain-file dir you serve or share):
# VAL_ARK_UPLOADS=$VAL_ARK_DATA/val-ark/uploads
#
# Explicit dirs to sweep (colon-separated); when set, overrides VAL_ARK_UPLOADS.
# VALARK_MODERATION_DIRS=/srv/uploads:/srv/dropbox
#
# Max files screened per sweep pass (bounds one cycle; the rest wait for the next).
# VALARK_MODERATION_SWEEP_MAX=200

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPTIONAL — raise GitHub API rate limits for link checks / release lookups.
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxx

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# REMOTE FLEET for the verification loop (space-separated user@host or host).
# Leave empty to skip remote checks. mDNS .local names and user@ip both work.
# Put YOUR hosts here in .env (this template ships only placeholders).
# VALARK_FLEET="node-a.local node-b.local user@10.0.0.20"
#
# Where the fleet mounts the Val Ark content (for the "fleet sees content" check).
# Defaults to VAL_ARK_DATA if unset.
# VALARK_FLEET_DATA=/mnt/valark
